  "motivation": "Kicking off animations after having reached a desired scroll position is a common pattern on the web. Achieving this requires JavaScript to know when to trigger an animation. However, in many cases, all the information needed for many use cases can be declaratively specified. This feature provides authors a robust, reliable, performant and convenient way to set up such animations in response to scrolling.",
